liberia and taiwan have normalized 
relations 12 years after the african nation switched recognition 
from taipei to the rival communist government in china officials 
say 
the late monday night announcement by foreign minister lien chan 
represents a breakthrough for the nationalist governments new 
flexible policy of seeking diplomatic ties with countries that 
already have relations with beijing 
lien attributed taiwans diplomatic victory to its making more 
progress politically economically and socially than communist 
china 
the official broadcasting corp of china quoting unnamed 
sources said taiwan had agreed to offer liberia a 200 million 
loan foreign ministry officials declined comment 
the reestablishment of ties between taiwan and liberia comes 
three months after taiwan established ties with grenada china 
subsequently suspended diplomatic relations with the tiny caribbean 
island 
there was no immediate reaction from beijing to liberias 
decision 
taiwans latest moves come after decades of diplomatic reversals 
in which the overwhelming majority of nations chose to recognize 
the communists in beijing instead of the nationalists in taipei 
both governments have claimed to be the legitimate ruler of all 
china since the communists defeated the nationalists in a civil war 
that ended in 1949 
the number of countries with formal ties to the nationalist 
government has dropped from more than 50 in 1949 to 24 not 
including liberia which is among the 134 countries that recognize 
china 
chan told a news conference monday night that taiwan and liberia 
would sign a formal communique on setting up diplomatic ties in a 
few days the two countries agreed to pursue normalization in 
january he said 
communist chinese leaders have criticized taiwans flexible 
diplomacy as a plan to promote two separate chinas a claim the 
nationalist officials deny 
liberia with a population of 25 million is an agricultural 
country that relies on the exports of coffee lumber and rubber 
liberia imported 24 million of industrial products from taiwan 
in 1988 its exports to taiwan totaled 270000 
