coggin said he witnessed incidents in which employees lunches 
were kept in a refrigerator along with aidsinfected blood samples 
a surgical assistant used a hallway telephone while wearing 
bloodsoaked gloves and janitors removed biohazardous waste in 
unprotected street clothes 
most of these workers recognize the potential danger and even 
lethal outcomes of a laboratory exposure to bloodborne viruses and 
agents but yield to the pressure of getting the work done 
quickly coggin said 
