that can cause aids as a result of workplace exposure and an 
estimated 12000 healthcare workers now contract hepatitis b every 
year because of occupational exposure 
according to the newspaper osha has proposed requiring 
gloves face shields gowns fluidresistant clothing and other 
equipment for any workers who might be exposed to potentially 
infectious materials 
employerpaid vaccinations of all employees whose jobs exposed 
