thousands of independent contractors it is expected to hire to 
manage the real estate and other assets it is inheriting from the 
thrifts 
david c cooke the agencys executive director said the rtc is 
trying to prevent improprieties but at the same time avoid defining 
conflict of interest so broadly that it is difficult to hire 
advisers and property managers 
its difficult cooke said in a recent interview many of 
the really big acknowledged experts have potential conflicts we 
need advice on how to sell real estate and the same contractors 
that would provide us advice are probably advising somebody 
else who may be interested in buying that real estate 
the code prohibits contractors from selfdealing favortism and 
conflicts of interest and sets up an agency board to rule on cases 
that arent black and white 
in another safeguard the management of the rtc is split in a 
unique arrangement designed to prevent abuse policies are 
formulated by a cabinetlevel board headed by treasury secretary 
nicholas f brady but the actual operations are being carried out 
by the federal deposit insurance corp the independent agency 
insuring bank and sampl deposits through a staff headed by cooke 
in the first few weeks of the rtcs existence that structure 
led to public squabbling between the fdic and the adminstration 
oversight board cooke said the tension was easing but members of 
congress are still concerned 
the one thing thats troubled me so far is the fighting 
between the fdic and the oversight board is that really 
resolved permanently or is it just quiescent said rep charles 
schumer dny a member of a house task force appointed to 
oversee the rtc 
however cooke said i think were working that out on 
day one theres a certain amount of tension because they may be 
thinking one thing and were thinking something entirely different 
time is making that better 
in its first two months of existence the rtc has spent 20 
billion 18 billion to close the 24 small sampls 83 billion to 
handle the five large institutions and several other 
notyetcompleted deals 85 billion to replace highcost 
deposits and 14 billion as a reserve fund to handle liquidity 
problems at failed but still open thrifts spokesman steve 
katsanos said tuesday 
