he had multiple other nontraceable contacts onenight stands 
hes fully cooperative but he doesnt know these other women he 
had casual sex with 
a private doctor referred the man to cedarssinai for aids 
testing but he wasnt hospitalized ho said 
hiv2 or human immunodeficiency virus type 2 was first 
described in 1985 in west african prostitutes who had no symptoms 
then was reported in 1986 in two west africans who suffered aids 
obrien said 
hiv1 and hiv2 both can cripple the bodys ability to fight 
disease leading to fatal infections and cancers 
the question that remains is whether it hiv2 can lead to 
immunodeficiency as quickly or as often as hiv1 which has 
caused aids in more than 105000 americans killing some 61000 of 
them obrien said 
the infected los angeles man has very low levels of hiv2 in his 
blood so the risk of transmission in casual sexual contacts is 
very low kerndt said 
he said the man may have been infected before coming to the 
country in 1979 or during a visit home in 1983 
kerndt said the infected man never donated blood has not used 
drugs intravenously nor has he engaged in any homosexual 
activity 
so far the risk to the blood supply is considered low because 
blood bank guidelines prohibit blood donations by west africans 
and because the test used to detect blood infected with hiv1 can 
detect 85 percent to 90 percent of samples of blood infected with 
hiv2 kerndt said 
hiv2 and hiv1 are equally common in the ivory coast and hiv2 
may be more common in guinea bissau and perhaps senegal obrien 
said adding that hiv2 infection also has been reported in europe 
south america and other parts of africa 
