international business machines corp says it 
has been awarded a patent for superconducting materials and said 
separately it had begun shipping a plugin chip for highspeed 
personal computers 
ibm said monday its us patent was granted for a group of 
superconducting materials that have no resistance to electricity at 
temperatures when cooled to 243 degrees below zero fahrenheit or 
colder 
one of the materials remains superconducting as warm as 234 
degrees below zero which ibm said is still the highest confirmed 
transition temperature for any stable superconductor 
the inventors are edward m engler victor y lee adel i 
nazzal and stuart sp parkin who work at ibms almaden research 
center in san jose calif they reported their work in february 
1988 and the patent was issued on sept 26 of this year 
the plugin chip is intel corps i486 microprocessor the 
fastest available for ibmstyle personal computers it comes on a 
power platform that ibm said could plug into one of its 
personal computers in place of the existing microprocessor 
ibm had promised delivery of the plugin chip by the end of the 
year it said it had installed the first one at continental bank 
corp in chicago 
