new home sales fell a slight 04 percent in 
august but remained over 750000 for the second straight month the 
government reported tuesday as buyers took advantage of lower 
interest rates 
analysts had forecast a steeper slide in august sales from a 
doubledigit gain in july the largest advance in three years they 
said the pace cannot be sustained but will remain healthy for the 
rest of the year 
the commerce department said that new singlefamily homes were 
sold at a seasonally adjusted rate of 755000 in august a 
relatively small drop from julys revised 758000 rate which was a 
161 percent increase over june 
the commerce report indicated new home sales were stronger 
throughout the summer than previously thought not only was the 
july figure revised upward so too were the may and june figures 
both of which totaled 653000 units 
