to cargo ships for transport to the soviet union 
shipments are to begin almost immediately he said 
the effect on the us chicken market will be very limited he 
said 
it wont do anything to the american market except add 
stability as any big contract does over a period of time tyson 
said in fact there wont be any disruption in the supply to our 
normal customers 
blair said the contract is with a company with which tyson 
normally competes in the united states he would not say whether 
the company was either conagra inc of omaha neb or perdue farms 
inc of salisbury md 
the multicompany arrangement he said arose because i dont 
think any single company would have the capacity to fulfill the 
contract without disruption of its normal operations 
he said that as far as he knew the arrangements with the 
soviet union involve no export subsidy by the us government the 
sale by tyson blair said was at us market prices as was the 
sale to the soviet union by the company with which tyson has 
contracted 
